1 make reference to or incorporate the provisions of this subsection, nor
2 shall the provisions of this subsection be construed to be any part of the
3 consideration of employment of any teacher, officer or other employee of
4 the board.
5 (e) (1) The board may transact all school district business and adopt
6 policies that the board deems appropriate to perform its constitutional duty
7 to maintain, develop and operate local public schools.
8 (2) The power granted by this subsection shall not be construed to
9 relieve a board from compliance with state law.
10 (3) The power granted by this subsection shall not be construed to
11 relieve any other unit of government of its duties and responsibilities that
12 are prescribed by law, nor to create any responsibility on the part of a
13 school district to assume the duties or responsibilities that are required of
14 another unit of government.
15 (3)(4) The board shall exercise the power granted by this subsection
16 by resolution of the board of education.
17 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 72-1145 is hereby amended to read as follows: 72-
18 1145. The board of education of any school district or the board of trustees
19 of any community junior college is hereby authorized to appropriate
20 money out of its general fund to pay the annual dues in the Kansas
21 association of school boards for membership in a not-for-profit
22 organization that provides guidance, resources and other services to
23 member school districts.
24 Sec. 3. K.S.A. 72-1416 is hereby amended to read as follows: 72-
25 1416. (a) The school board shall have control of the school-district school
26 district property, including:
27 (1) The school building or buildings, schoolgrounds school grounds
28 and all buildings and structures erected thereon,; and
29 (2) all furniture, fittings, and equipment, such as including books,
30 maps, charts, and instructional apparatus.
31 (b) Members of the school board may access school district property,
32 including any school buildings and attendance centers, during school
33 hours or when there are school or community activities on such property.
34 (c) The school board may open the schoolhouse school building for
35 public purpose, under such pursuant to rules and regulations as adopted by
36 the board shall adopt.
37 (d) The board may:
38 (1) Enter into contracts with public library boards to authorize such
39 boards to use the library facilities of the school district to supplement the
40 facilities of the public library;
41 (2) make suchadopt rules and regulations relating to such school
42 libraries as they shall deem necessary; and
43 (3) appoint librarians.

